kanji.meaning: be defeated; lose; overlook; error; fault
kanji.examples:
失望 (しつぼう) disappointment; despair
失業 (しつぎょう) losing one's job; becoming unemployed
失敗 (しっぱい) failure
失礼 (しつれい) impolite; rude | excuse me; I'm leaving
kanji.components: 丿: katakana no radical (no. 4) 夫: husband; man
kanji.koohii1: The drop falling here is the husband´s toupee... he´s already lost his hair once/ now he´s losing it again. Such is life/ I suppose.
kanji.koohii2: Note: Heisig´s stroke order is wrong. It´s the same as vermilion/ drop first. Homer loses/drops his wedding ring.

kanji_info.image_description: A tiny, sad husband (夫) with a big, teary katakana no (丿) hanging over his head, symbolizing defeat. The background is a field of missed opportunities, symbolized by scattered coins and broken arrows.

kanji.examples:
守る (まもる) to protect; to guard; to uphold; to follow
留守 (るす) absence; being away from home
kanji.components: 宀: shaped crown; katakana u radical (no. 40) 寸: measurement; foot/10
kanji.koohii1: A GUARD is usually 'glued' to the house he watches.
kanji.koohii2: A guard provides a measure of security to those under a roof.

kanji_info.image_description: A giant, protective  katakana u (宀) standing proudly on a giant foot (寸), shielding a village from a storm. The u has a  small, vigilant face, and the foot is sturdy and strong.

kanji.examples:
完了 (かんりょう) completion
完全 (かんぜん) completeness
完成 (かんせい) completion; accomplishment
kanji.components: 宀: shaped crown; katakana u radical (no. 40) 元: beginning; former time; origin
kanji.koohii1: Make the perfect impression in the beginning by removing your shoes upon entering a Japanese home.
kanji.koohii2: In the beginning/ Adam and Eve had a home in Eden. It was perfect.

kanji_info.image_description: A majestic crown (宀) with a shimmering katakana u (宀)  sitting on top,  sitting on top of a large, golden spiral representing the beginning (元).  The whole structure is bathed in a warm light, symbolizing completion.

kanji.examples: 警官 (けいかん) police officer
kanji.components: 宀: shaped crown; katakana u radical (no. 40) 口: mouth
kanji.koohii1: No one likes classical music anymore. Our Maestro is here at home without his baton sighing sadly before he heads off for another day as his new job as a bureaucrat.
kanji.koohii2: Bureaucrat/ def: The maestro without a baton/ the one who orchestrates oppressive rules/ regulations and taxes on every household.

kanji_info.image_description: A regal crown (宀) with a katakana u (宀)  sitting on top, perched on a giant,  speaking mouth (口) that looks like a loudspeaker, booming out government decrees. The crown and the mouth are adorned with intricate details, highlighting the power and formality of the bureaucrat.

kanji.kun_reading: さだ・か/さだ・まる/さだ・める
kanji.examples:
勘定 (かんじょう) calculation; computation; consideration
否定 (ひてい) denial; repudiation
安定 (あんてい) stability; steadiness
定期 (ていき) fixed period; fixed term
決定 (けってい) decision
予定 (よてい) plans; schedule | expectation; estimate
kanji.components: 宀: shaped crown; katakana u radical (no. 40) 疋: head; counter for animals
kanji.koohii1: In The Karate Kid/ the boy must prove his determination by MENDING his teacher´s HOUSE in various ways.
kanji.koohii2: People who decide to renovate (ooh/ that´s a fancy word/ let´s say 'mend') their houses must be very determined DIYers. (Using DIY helps me remember this story when I see DEtermine).

kanji_info.image_description: A crown (宀) sits on top of a majestic,  headless beast (疋). The crown, shaped like a katakana u (宀),  is a powerful symbol of control, representing the  decision-making power.

sentences.sentence_japanese: プロジェクトはついに完成しました。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: The project is finally complete.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 仕事を終えて達成感を感じます。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: I feel a sense of accomplishment after finishing my work.

sentences.sentence_japanese: 新しい建物の建設は完成に近づいています。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: The construction of the new building is nearing completion.

sentences.sentence_japanese: タスクを完了したら、お祝いできます。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 絵は完成して、展示の準備ができました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 安定した仕事を見つけたいです。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 経済はようやく安定の兆しを見せています。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 彼は安定した幸せな生活を送っています。

sentences.sentence_japanese: その会社は財務の安定性で知られています。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 天気は、今は安定してきました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 今朝、鍵をなくしました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 彼は電車の中で財布をなくしました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: その会社は昨年、多くの資金を失いました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 彼は会社のリストラで仕事を失いました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 失業後に新しい仕事を見つけるのは難しいです。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 政府は失業した人々に支援を提供しています。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 彼女は自分に対する告発を否定しました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: そのニュースに驚いたことは否定できません。
sentences.sentence_english_translation: I cannot deny that I was surprised by the news.

sentences.sentence_japanese: その科学者の理論は、科学界からの否定に遭いました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 彼はその犯罪への関与を否定しました。

sentences.sentence_japanese: 否定に遭うとしても、自分の意見を表現することを恐れないで。

vocabulary.meaning: to protect; to guard; to uphold; to follow

sentences.sentence_japanese: その会社は進捗状況を話し合うために定期的に会議を開きます。

short_text_with_quiz.text_japanese:
数か月前に仕事を失ってから、ずっと新しい仕事を探しています。家族を養うために、安定した収入を得られる仕事を見つけたいと思っています。前の仕事は悪くありませんでしたが、いつも同じようなことを繰り返しているような気がしていました。自分を見失っているような気がして、楽しくありませんでした。

情熱を注げる仕事、本当に心を込めることができる仕事を見つけたいと思っています。簡単ではないことは分かっていますが、大好きな仕事を見つける決意をしています。自分自身を成長させることができる仕事を見つけたいです。私は、努力することを恐れませんが、自分のやっていることに満足していることを確認したいと思っています。人生で何をしたいのか、長い間考えてきました。そして、私は世界に貢献したいという結論に至りました。自分のスキルと才能を使って他の人を助けられる仕事を見つけたいと思っています。

きっと良い仕事が見つかると思いますが、少し気持ちが落ち込み始めています。私を生き生きとさせてくれる仕事を見つけたいです。

なぜ自分がこんなにも頑張っているのか、常に自分に言い聞かせなければなりません。お金のためだけではありません。世界に貢献するため、そして本当に大好きなものを見つけるためです。きっと良い仕事があるはずです。見つけるまで諦めません。
short_text_with_quiz.text_english:
I lost my job a few months ago, and I've been looking for a new one ever since.  I want to find a job that will give me a stable income so I can provide for my family.  My old job was okay, but I always felt like I was just going through the motions. I felt like I was losing myself, and I wasn't happy. 

I want to find a job that I'm passionate about, something that I can really put my heart into. I know it won't be easy, but I'm determined to find a job that I love.  I want to find something that will allow me to grow as a person.  I'm not afraid of hard work, but I want to make sure that I'm happy with what I'm doing.  I've spent a lot of time thinking about what I want to do with my life, and I've come to the conclusion that I want to make a difference in the world.  I want to find a job that allows me to use my skills and talents to help others.  I'm confident that I'll find the right job eventually, but I'm starting to feel a little discouraged.  I want to find something that makes me feel alive. 

I need to keep reminding myself why I'm doing this. It's not just about the money, it's about making a difference in the world, and about finding something that I truly love.  I know that the right job is out there, and I'm not going to give up until I find it.

song_lyrics.lyrics_english_translation: The year is almost over, but there are still things I haven't finished. I have to work hard and get it all done. I'm a little worried because I'm not sure if I can keep up the pace. I don't want to lose the stability I've built. But I have to keep going, with the intention of achieving my goals. I'll solve the problems that come my way and keep moving forward. I want to work hard and make this year a success. I hope to eat good food, sleep soundly, and have a fulfilling year.
